The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Sunday, December 01, 2002 				 Title for Shivika
 BY A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Nov. 30: Shivika Burman beat Danielle Jones to emerge champion in the girls under-14 singles category of the floodlit hardcourt tennis meet. Shivika won the final 6-0, 6-2. 																								OTHER RESULTS																								Boys under-18 singles (quarters)  Sabyasachi Bose bt Baibhav Das 6-1, 6-0; Indradeep Mitra bt Samridh Burman 6-3, 6-2; Samrat Ghosh bt Abdesh Roy 6-3, 7-5; Akshay Bajoria bt Arup Mallick 7-6, 4-6, 6-1. Ladies singles handicap (semis)  Ankita Dokania bt Akriti Dokania 6-3, 7-5. Veterans doubles (above 45)  D. Sircar amp; S. Sircar bt S.S. Madan amp; Sharad Verma 6-4, 6-2. 																								Badminton coaching																								Romen Ghosh, a former Indian badminton international and Arjuna Award-winner, has set up a coaching centre of excellence. The centre will be inaugurated at Khudiram Anushilan Kendra on Wednesday while the process of selection of trainees will begin the day after.																								Trainees aged between eight and 25 years, will be divided into three categories  beginners, intermediates and medal-hopes. It will be run four days a week throughout the year and many shuttlers from the state  present and past, will be involved.																								Ghosh hoped to turn the centre into an academy in future. 																								TODAY IN SPORT																								TENNIS: Floodlit meet at Saturday Club from 4 pm.
